.Dt YIELD 2
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm yield
.Nd yield execution to another lightweight process
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In unistd.h
.Ft "void"
.Fn "yield" "void"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn yield
function causes the current lightweight process to yield its execution in favor
of another lightweight process with the same or greater priority.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr thr_yield 3C
